  <h3>Instructions: 400 to 500 words</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>The arc.</strong> Map the development of your thread across four weeks of coverage. Name the key turning points and what drove them: new evidence, new sources, editorial decisions, or shifts in algorithmic distribution.</li>
    <li><strong>The voices.</strong> Who has spoken in your beat's coverage across four weeks, named specifically? Who has been described but not directly heard? Who does not appear at all? Propose a structural explanation for the pattern.</li>
    <li><strong>The AI footprint.</strong> Where has AI touched your beat's coverage over four weeks — in how stories were found, summarized, distributed, or generated? Offer at least two specific observations about what AI did, not one general statement about what AI does.</li>
    <li><strong>The analytical claim.</strong> Two to three sentences stating your argument about how this coverage works, a claim about structure, not a judgment about quality. It should be specific enough that someone who followed your beat could meaningfully disagree with it.</li>
  </ol>
</div>
<div class="block">
  <h3>Rubric</h3>
  <table class="rubric">
    <tr><th>Element</th><th>Expectations</th><th>Points</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Arc mapping</td><td>Four or more coverage items cited with dates. Turning points identified with specific causes, not general observations.</td><td class="pts">25</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Voice inventory</td><td>Named sources present and absent, with a structural explanation attempted, not "the media ignored X" but a specific reason why.</td><td class="pts">25</td></tr>
    <tr><td>AI footprint</td><td>At least two specific observations about AI's role in four weeks of coverage, not general claims, specific instances.</td><td class="pts">25</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Analytical claim</td><td>Clear, arguable claim about structure, distinct from evaluation of quality, and specific enough to be disputed on the basis of evidence.</td><td class="pts">25</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td></td><td class="pts"><strong>100</strong></td></tr>
  </table>
</div>
</div>

